ral processes. Moreover, these essays elucidate the links between humans and the lands they inhabit, both then and now.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aEcocriticism. 0aEnglish literatureyEarly modern, 1500-1700xHistory and criticism. 0aLiterature and sciencezEnglandxHistoryy16th century. 0aLiterature and sciencezEnglandxHistoryy17th century. 0aNature in literature. 0aSoil and civilization. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Renaissance.2bisacsh1 aBadcoe, Tamsin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBotelho, Keith M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDolan, Frances E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEklund, Hillary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEklund, Hillary, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGoldstein, David B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Bonnie Lander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartin, Randall, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Dair, Sharon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReid, Lindsay Ann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWakeman, Rob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271093529zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271093529423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271093529/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK